rComments: textbook for this class is a must. prof Rodrigues' lectures are short and to the point and he explains the key concepts clearly. very helpful during office hours for both lecture and lab material. tutorials were kinda lame but attendance was mandatory. the lab report was killer. get writing help if writing lab report is not your thing.

Course content wasn't too interesting in my personal opinion but it's a mandatory course so just suck it up and get through it. Prof Rodrigues' lectures were clear, easy to follow + understand and his tests were fair. Hope the department gives him this course to teach again next year!

Anuar is a precious gem of a professor and I love him to pieces. He's super friendly, super helpful, and knows what he's talking about at all times. He's one of the most approachable people in the Biology department, and honestly I hope he teaches lots more courses here in the future.
